race.comment: JOCUND (6) resumes heavily bet at Taree and delivered her Maiden. She has been building to that and will appreciate the longer sprint. This doesn't look much harder and she'll present fitter with a 3kg claim. LA CACHE A VIN (7) has been threatening another win and will find this easier than Ballina. Has a wide gate to contend with but can feature with average luck. NORTHERN BOOGIE (9) placed in a CL1 at Taree first-up. He's been struggling to find his best and may hand turned the corner. He will have come on and can make the finish. OUR SILVER LININGS (2) had been tracking well in better races before a plain effort last time. Better stepping up to this distance and she has to be considered. PRIDE OF LANKA (8) tries hard and is on a quick backup. Hard to see him winning, but he should be around the mark.
